<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Arctostaphylos</i> <i>hookeri</i> is dominant or co-dominant in the shrub canopy with <i>Adenostoma</i> <i>fasciculatum</i>, <i>Arctostaphylos</i> <i>crustacea</i>, <i>Arctostaphylos</i> <i>montereyensis</i>, <i>Arctostaphylos</i> <i>pajaroensis</i>, <i>Artemisia</i> <i>californica</i>, <i>Baccharis</i> <i>pilularis</i>, <i>Ceanothus</i> <i>cuneatus</i> var. <i>rigidus</i>, <i>Dendromecon</i> <i>rigida</i>, <i>Diplacus</i> <i>aurantiacus</i>, <i>Eriodictyon</i> <i>californicum</i>, <i>Frangula</i> <i>californica</i>, <i>Garrya</i> <i>fremontii</i>, <i>Heteromeles</i> <i>arbutifolia</i>, <i>Lotus</i> <i>scoparius</i>, <i>Lupinus</i> <i>chamissonis</i>, <i>Salvia</i> <i>mellifera</i> and <i>Toxicodendron</i> <i>diversilobum</i>. Emergent trees may be present at low cover, including <i>Pinus</i> <i>radiata</i> or <i>Quercus</i> <i>agrifolia</i>. </div>
</div>

		
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Shrubs < 1.5 m; canopy is intermittent. Herbaceous layer is sparse. </div>
</div>

		
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Sandstone outcrops, mesas, ridge tops, and upper slopes. Soils are typically shallow and gravelly or sandy.  </div>
</div>

		
